==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antozone
<hw>Ant*o"zone</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>anti-</ets> + <ets>ozone</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
compound formerly supposed to be modification of oxygen, but now known
to be hydrogen dioxide; -- so called because apparently antagonistic to
ozone, converting it into ordinary oxygen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

